Package org.microbean.qualifier

Interface Qualified<K extends Constable & Comparable<K>,V extends Constable,T>

Type Parameters:
K - the type borne by the keys of the Qualifiers in this Qualified
V - the type borne by the values of the Qualifiers in this Qualified
T - the type of the object that is qualified; note that if it does not extend Constable then a Qualified bearing it will return an empty Optional from its describeConstable() method
All Superinterfaces:
Constable
All Known Implementing Classes:
Qualified.Record
@Experimental public interface Qualified<K extends Constable & Comparable<K>,V extends Constable,T> extends Constable
A Constable pairing of a Qualifiers and an Object that is qualified by them.
Author:
Laird Nelson

    • describeConstable

      @OverridingEncouraged default Optional<? extends ConstantDesc> describeConstable()
      Returns an Optional containing the nominal descriptor for this instance, if one can be constructed, or an empty Optional if one cannot be constructed.

      The default implementation of this method returns an Optional<? extends ConstantDesc> that is computed from only the return value of the qualifiers() method and the return value of the qualified() method. This may or may not be sufficient for any given subclass' semantics.

      Specified by:
      describeConstable in interface Constable
      Returns:
      an Optional containing the nominal descriptor for this instance, if one can be constructed, or an empty Optional if one cannot be constructed; never null
      Idempotency:
      This method is, and its overrides must be, idempotent and deterministic.
      Nullability:
      This method does not, and its overrides must not, return null.
      Thread Safety:
      This method is, and its overrides must be, safe for concurrent use by multiple threads.
